<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,775,861,1045]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,253,861,885]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,246,861,885]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
— Relatively small belostomatids, body length less than 
<quantity box="[237,316,893,917]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
. Body ovate, dorsoventrally flattened (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[834,870,2035,2057]" captionTargetBox="[835,1473,1263,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-665@2.[835,1475,1263,2011]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Diplonychus rusticus (Fabricius), male, specimen from Philippines, Luzon." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351512/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Head produced ahead of eyes, apex sub-triangular; eyes with inner margins convergent; head width less than twice the maximum interocular width. Fore tarsi bearing two claws; middle and hind tibiae not flattened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,775,1085,1333]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,263,1085,1109]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,256,1085,1109]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Discussion</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
— This genus contains relatively small, ovate, brown belostomatids that are often extremely common along the margins of ponds and other standing water habitats. A confusingly large number of generic and specific names have been applied to the species currently held in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1833" box="[633,768,1214,1237]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Diplonychus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[633,768,1214,1237]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Diplonychus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For the one species occurring in the region under study, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[136,361,1278,1301]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Diplonychus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rusticus">
<emphasis box="[136,361,1278,1301]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Diplonychus rusticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the relevant nomenclatural synonymy is provided below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
